"08/10/2020 03:56am","83.79.152.69","0","Chef Cuisinier","candidature spontanée","Dear Sir or Madam, 
 
I am Pau Luca Marques, graduated from the University College of Hospitality Management and Culinary Arts of Sant Pol de Mar’s Hotel-School (currently one of the 50 best universities in the world in hospitality and catering).

In the last year, there have been professional development sessions in which we have gone through a selection process to be able to enter a company and grow within it. 

After the interviews of 200 students of the Mandarin Oriental, I am part of a selection of 5 candidates. 

Unfortunately, the Coronavirus has severely damaged the restaurant industry, in particular the Mandarin Oriental of Barcelona forced to close temporarily.
  
I currently live in GY (Geneva) with my partner of Swiss nationality and I have the B permit
Given the situation, I consider being a private chef would be a dream to me creating new dishes and developing my creativity always counting on the preferences of my employer and I would be thrilled to have the opportunity and to make people happy with my dishes. 

I am very attracted to the type of cuisine where delicate dishes convey a complex simplicity with modern touches and each ingredient offers the maximum intensity of its flavour.

I am therefore looking for fitting inside of a family where I can use and develop my skills while growing personally and professionally. I would have no problem if it was a 24h job I am 100% dedicated and cooking its what makes me happy.

I will explain a summary of my professional experience in more detail in my CV:

I had the opportunity to develop my vocation for the culinary arts in different types of kitchen.

First in a food truck (La caseta verda) where I learned to work with a large volume of work since we made about 100-150 covers per service.

After a few months I worked in El Perlin in Berlin, Germany, led by the famous painter Mariano Rinaldi Goni and the oenologist Yurgen Stumpf, where we worked on the design of the menus of each week based on seasonal and 0 km products.

I learned to develop my creativity and to perfect my knowledge. 

When i came back to spain, I did an internship at ""Fonda de España"" (by Martin Berasategui), where I learned a lot about haute and gastronomic cuisine.

I consider each dish a unique experience trying to convey emotions and sensations that go beyond simple food.



Then I got the job as chef the partie at Fierro Parrilla specialized in aged and large pieces of meat I had the opportunity to deepen and master my knowledge about the meat I could also develop my creativity a lot because one of my responsibilities was the one to creating three new deserts every two weeks I was in charge of the cold area the pastry and deserts and the Josper grill.


In attached files, you can find my curriculum vitae and a recommendation letter in both original and translated versions, from the executive Chef German Espinosa of ""Fonda de España"".

Please feel free to email me or call if you need any further information’s.

Thank you for your consideration and I am looking forwards to hearing from you soon.

Sincerely,

Pau Luca Marques
pauluca00@gmail.com 
+41 79 726 47 12
