"10/22/2020 04:05am","46.253.189.79","0","Autres","Estate Manager","Dear Madam, dear Sir, 
 
I am writing to apply for the position of Estate Manager. This application may sound surprising considering my profile and experience, but I have decided to leave the Bar of Geneva and reorient my career, to support and provide high quality legal and administrative services to a single client base, such as a family. 

Since being admitted to the Geneva Bar in 2009, I have worked as a general practitioner in several Swiss law firms in Geneva, with ad hoc missions in Dubai and Nassau.

Always eager to tackle new challenges, I have pursued my career as a generalist, in order to continue serving the different legal needs of a mixed and varied client base, with whom I built strong relationships of trust throughout the years. Being a general advisor to these clients has also enabled me to develop big picture thinking and all-round skills, allowing me to take care of the legal and administrative day-to-day needs of our clients. It has further enabled me to supervise and manage complex cases/projects, and delegate specific missions to specialists and/or colleagues from other jurisdictions, when necessary.

I am now looking to invest myself in a more exclusive environment, with a more practical and hands-on approach, and a chance to establish a long-term relationship of trust with a family. I am therefore very interested by the opportunity to accomplish the broad variety of tasks enumerated in the job description you have published, knowing that these would be undertaken with professionalism, assiduity, and discretion. Moreover, I believe that I could bring a substantial added value to this role, by accomplishing the administrative, financial, and managerial tasks and duties enumerated in the job description - and hopefully much more - with the solid all-round legal experience, skills, and contacts I have gained throughout my career.

Although I have no specific experience in estate management, I allow myself to highlight that I have had, through my past mandates, several perspectives into the various needs and requirements of the properties of our clients, both in Switzerland and abroad. In addition, I accomplished an eight month training course in a reputable and prestigious hotel in the Sultanate of Oman, which gave me a solid introduction to hospitality needs, that would also be involved in this position .  I am therefore confident that I could fulfill the role as Estate Manager to the full satisfaction of the family.

I thank you for your consideration of my application and remain at your disposal should you wish to meet in person. 
 
Kind regards, 
 
Anita La Roche
