"03/07/2022 08:33am","165.225.94.102","0","Assistant personnel","Candidature Spontanée","Dear Sir/Madam,

Swiss citizen, I am well-travelled thanks to my 6 years of expatriation (1 year in Chicago, 1.5 years in NYC,  2 years in Washington DC and 1 year în Fairfax, VA) and have always worked in an international environment. Therefore, I am able to relate to expatriates' private and professional needs, while having a solid knowledge of the Swiss cultural, economic and financial institutions. 

Having worked for the Swiss Federal Department of Foreign Affairs, I have a good understanding of the protocol and etiquette and can rapidly adapt to a new environment with stakeholders of different cultures and hierarchical levels.

I speak and write French and English fluently. My German is a bit rusty, but should I have to use it more often, it would come back in no time thanks to my original B2 level. Italian remains conversational despite my 5 years studying it, as I have not used it much since.

Under ""Education"", you will see that I started my career in Hospitality and should you want to see my work certificates (no longer on my CV), you will notice that I spent over 2 year in two different hotels and obtained a diploma of Hotel Secretary-Receptionist back in 1990.

I also obtained a diploma (Brevet fédéral) in Public Relations while working 100% as Internal Communication and Event Manager, structure that I created from scratch.

On a private level, I raised my daughter alone while working 100% since she is 4 y.o. She is now 23 y.o. and has just gotten her Bachelor from the Ecole Hôtelière de Lausanne (EHL) Business Management School. 

Even if I have no experience working for a Family Office as such, throughout my professional and personal experience, I have acquired all the competences and knowledge that made me a people, service and solution-oriented professional.

Moreover, my daughter is about to leave our home, so I am ready to work outside ""official"" office hours and travel to get the job done. I would also consider a position in Europe or in the US.

I really hope you will consider this spontaneous application and look forward to hearing from you.

Kind regards.

Nathalie Bruelhart
